\title{Conjugacy class of an element}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-16}
\taxon{definition}
\MML{group_3}{def 8}{K}
\import{iaa-0001}

\p{Let #{G} be a [[gr-000G]]. Let #{g\in G} be an element. We define the \define{Conjugacy Class} of #{g} to be the subset #{\Cl(g)} of #{G} equal to
##{\Cl(g)=\{g^{b}\in G\mid b\in G\}.}
In other words, #{\Cl(g)} is the set of elements #{a\in G} such that #{a} [is conjugate to](gr-0028) #{g}.}